RIYADH: Saudi Advanced Petrochemical Co. will increase its capital by 20 percent to SR2.6 billion ($693 million) through granting bonus shares. Shareholders are set to receive one bonus share for every five shares held, a bourse filing showed. The move comes in line with the Jubail-based firm’s expansion efforts. In a statement, the company said the move aims to support its “capital base to match the size of company assets.” 